Described species .— Apart from the type species, 11 species have been described in
Sphingius
and Thamphilus from a region stretching from India to Viet Nam and the Malay Peninsula; I add five new species here. Four of the Indian species were described by Gravely; two of the latter, emended by Majumder and Tikader, 1991, probably do not fit in the genus and are left out here ( I suspect that
S. longipes
belongs in
Systaria ). Sphingius thecatus Thorell, 1890
, ♀, Malaysia, Penang;
